The paper deals with the design of wireless systems with stringent requirements on latency and reliability, which are key concerns in the fields of information theory (cs.IT), networking (cs.NI), and control systems (cs.SY). The paper also discusses the use of multi-antenna and frequency-division techniques, which are relevant to multimedia systems (cs.MM) and signal processing (cs.AR).
